"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"**前言：**这是**翻译角**第三篇Web3文章，翻译角是风哥介绍海外加密社区优秀文章的窗口，做这个版块一方面是为提升个人视野，另一方面是为提升英文阅读与翻译能力，可预见的未来，币圈将成为英语匮乏者的荒漠，不持续进化的人将被淘汰出局。\\n\\n另外，如遇优秀项目，也会对项目白皮书进行翻译与介绍。需要说明的是，翻译的这些文章不一定取得原作者同意，但会对作者进行背景调查与文字介绍，这些介绍与广告无关。\\n\\n**本文作者**：Derick David（德里克·大卫），大卫是一位高级产品设计师，初创企业咨询师与创业者，也是一位创新商业领域与科技领域的顶尖作家。\\n\\n**原文标题**：What is Web3? Explained Simply To a 12-Year-Old\\n\\n**原文链接**：<https://drckangelo.medium.com/what-is-web3-explained-simply-to-a-12-year-old-486bbc509ac7>\\n\\n**发布时间**：2021年11月15日\\n\\n**阅读提示：**下划线词组代表重点行业词汇，**黑色加粗代表重点单词与词组**，**红色加粗代表疑难词汇。**\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/6pZLnLIgtSHRRdJ3rH1ti.png?height=466&width=700)\\n\\n**正文：**\\n\\nWeb3 on Instagram. Web3 on Clubhouse. Web3 on Twitter. What’s this Web3? Aside from the obvious fact that it’s the next **evolution of Web2**, what does it consists of?\\n\\n人们在Instagram、俱乐部、推特上讨论Web3，什么是Web3？除了这是Web2的下一次进化这一显而易见的事实之外，它还包括什么？ \\n\\nWeb2, in a simple version, is the internet that we now see and use in the present day. Centralized. Read. Write. **Lately**, my LinkedIn and Twitter have been talking nothing but Web3. Of course, this got me curious, so I decided to dig deeper and actually understand what Web3 is. Given the way our society is **progressing with** cryptocurrencies, NFTs, and decentralization technologies, I found it worthy to learn it. Bitcoin has **played a major role** in jumpstarting the Web3 ecosystem.\\n\\nWeb2是一个简单的版本，是我们现在看到和使用的互联网，是我们使用中心化的方式进行阅读与写作的地方，最近，我的LinkedIn和Twitter只谈论Web3，它成功勾起了我的好奇心，所以我决定深入挖掘，真正理解Web3到底是什么。考虑到我们的社会在加密货币、NFT和去中心化技术方面的进步，学习Web3变得十分有意义。比特币在启动Web3生态系统方面发挥了重要作用。 \\n\\nIn an article by C**hris Dixon and Packy McCormick in [The Economist](https://www.economist.com/the-world-ahead/2021/11/08/chris-dixon-and-packy-mccormick-on-the-future-of-crypto)** it’s mentioned,\\n\\n> Because of the success of bitcoin, the pioneering cryptocurrency launched in 2008, many people associate blockchains **primarily** with money and finance. But the applications of blockchains are much broader.\\n\\nChris Dixon和Packy McCormick在《经济学人》上的一篇文章《[Chris Dixon与Packy McCormick对加密世界未来的看法](https://www.bitsmart.us/defi/chris-dixon-and-packy-mccormick-on-the-future-of-crypto)》中提到：\\n\\n> **由于2008年推出的首创加密货币比特币的成功，许多人主要将区块链与货币和金融联系起来，但事实上区块链的应用要广泛得多。** \\n\\nWhat is Blockchain again in simple words?\\n\\n* A digital ledger composed of blocks; each block **bundles** date of a transaction\\n* Whenever someone updates a piece of data, a request goes to every user or person for approval\\n* Updates get reflected in the system only after at least 50% of the users or people have **approved the request**\\n* Instead of all the information being stored on just one file, each person or user has an exact copy\\n\\n**简单地说，区块链又是什么？**\\n\\n* 由区块组成的数字账本；每个区块绑定一个交易日期；\\n* 每当有人更新数据时，都会向每个用户或个人发出请求以获得批准；\\n* 只有在至少50%的用户或人员同意后，才会允许系统级进行更新升级；\\n* 不是所有信息都存储在一个文件中，而是每个人或用户都有一个精确的副本 \\n\\nAs you can see already, it has its powerful advantages. It is a **tamperproof and trustworthy** way of keeping and storing information. The control lies in the hands of all the users using the application instead of one central database or **intermediary** that can be changed anytime, by anyone with proper access.\\n\\n正如你看到的那样，区块链具备强大的优势，它是一种防篡改、值得信赖的信息保存和存储方式。控制权掌握在使用应用程序的所有用户手中，而不是像Web2那样被一个中央数据库或中介控制，任何具有适当访问权限的人都可以随时篡改。 \\n\\nWhat started as **solely** Bitcoin for Web3 will grow so much bigger in the new decade.\\n\\n一开始只有比特币的Web3生态，将在接下来的十年中茁壮成长逐渐繁荣。\\n\\nWe’re talking about a multitude of applications that are applicable pretty everywhere in our society. **Albert Einstein** once said in his life that is pretty much applicable nowadays.\\n\\n当下，我们正在谈论的应用程序，它们在我们的社会中几乎无处不在。阿尔伯特·爱因斯坦曾经说过，这一点在今天非常适用。 \\n\\n> If you can’t explain it simply,\\n\\n> you don’t understand it well enough.\\n>\\n> **如果你不能用简洁的语言解释清楚，**\\n\\n> **说明你还不够了解。** \\n\\n**Part of actually learning is understanding a subject enough to be able to explain it in a simple manner.**\\n\\n实际上，我们学习的一部分目的是能够理解一个主题，以便使其能够以简单的方式向外人解释清楚。 \\n\\nIn this article, we’ll do our best to explain Web3 for you in the simplest of ways, that even a 12-year-old kid will understand. Let’s get it on.\\n\\n本文，我们将尽最大努力以最简单的方式为您解释Web3，即使是12岁的孩子也能理解。让我们开始吧。 \\n\\n \\n\\n**1、Key points about Web3（关于Web3的要点）**\\n\\n1）Web3 is a protocol for publishing and **consuming** data, first and foremost prepared to be distributed peer-to-peer\\n\\n2）It’s a software package designed to **create interfaces, tools, and services**\\n\\n3）This **radically** simpler approach to **elevating** promising new models of internet\\n\\nIn short, Web3 is a decentralized web and unlike Web2 who runs servers on **multiple centralized servers**, Web3 instead runs on [blockchains](https://medium.com/swlh/what-is-blockchain-simply-explained-by-a-15-year-old-941489219704), driven by peer-to-peer networks.\\n\\n1）Web3是一种用于发布和消费数据的协议，首要任务是以点对点的方式分发数据；\\n\\n2）它是一个设计用于创建接口、工具和服务的软件包；\\n\\n3）Web3是革新互联网新模式的较为简单的方法；\\n\\n简言之，Web3是一个去中心化网络，与在多个中心化服务器上运行的Web2不同，取而代之的是，Web3在由点对点驱动网络驱动的区块链上运行。 \\n\\n \\n\\n**2、Evolutionary stages（演化阶段）**\\n\\nBefore we move to Web3, let’s go back to history and review Web1.\\n\\n在我们转到Web3之前，让我们回到历史并回顾Web1。 \\n\\nWeb1, which is **diffused** from the 90s to mid-2000s is an internet that is one **dimensional**. Back then, websites only had one function, to display a list of information. So, you can read it. There’s no posting, sharing, and interacting with other people, because it hasn’t been thought out yet.\\n\\n从90年代到2000年代中期，Web1是一个一维的互联网。当时，网站只有一个功能，即显示信息列表。所以，你可以阅读它。没有发布、分享和与其他人互动，因为这还没有被考虑出来。 \\n\\nIt’s the era of **read**.\\n\\n这是阅读的时代。 \\n\\nWeb2, which is diffused from the mid-2000s to late 2010s is an internet that is two dimensional. Example websites are Facebook, Instagram, Snapchat had multiple functions. Aside from reading information from their platform, you can also post your own content so other people or users can read yours too and vice versa.\\n\\nWeb2是一种二维互联网，从21世纪中期到20世纪头十年广泛传播。例如Facebook、Instagram、Snapchat都有多种功能。除了从他们的平台上阅读信息外，你还可���发布自己的内容，这样其他人或用户也可以阅读你的内容，反之亦然。 \\n\\nIt’s the era of **read** and **write**.\\n\\n这是一个读写的时代。 \\n\\nWeb3, which is now being diffused from the early 2020s up to the next decades is an internet that is not only **three-dimensional** but potentially, multi-dimensional. Thus, Facebook with its Metaverse **initiative**.\\n\\nWeb3从20世纪20年代初一直传播到未来几十年，它不仅是一个三维的互联网，而且可能是多维的。因此，脸谱网的Metaverse计划。 \\n\\nExample technologies are NFTs and Cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin and Dogecoin. Take note, there’s one important **backbone** for Web3 to happen, decentralization. Decentralization means there’s not a centralized source of assets like money. An example would be our modern banks. With Web3, we don’t need banks because the technology allows itself to develop from users collectively.\\n\\n以NFT和加密货币（比特币和Dogecoin）为例，去中心化是Web3的重要支柱，这点值得注意，去中心化意味着没有资金这样的集中资产来源。我们的现代银行就是一个例子。有了Web3，我们不需要银行，因为这项技术允许自己从用户集体开发。 \\n\\nWeb3 is the era of **read**, **write**, and **own**.\\n\\nWeb3是一个读、写和拥有的时代。 \\n\\n \\n\\n**3、Why is Web3 powerful?（ 为什么Web3强大？ ）**\\n\\nWell, let’s just say Web3 gives power to people, not to institutions. You can’t be cheated, stolen, or broken. Web3 nowadays is becoming more of a **philosophical** and political innovation than technological.\\n\\n好吧，我们就说Web3给人权力，而不是给机构。你不能被欺骗，被偷，或被破坏。如今，Web3更多地是一种哲学和政治创新，而不是技术创新。 \\n\\nThis shows its true power to **revolutionize** the entire world. It’s what happens when you use technology in the right way.\\n\\n这显示了其真正的力量，以革命整个世界。这就是当你以正确的方式使用技术时会发生的事情。 \\n\\n**Web3 is already being used** to build powerful decentralized applications. These apps are removing middlemen from large industries.\\n\\nWeb3已经被用于构建功能强大的去中心化用程序。这些应用正在将中间商从大型行业中移除。 \\n\\nFor example, one project is working towards removing the need for ride-hailing companies by using a decentralized Ride Market DApp.\\n\\n例如，一个项目正在通过使用去中心化的打车DApp，以消除对出租车公司的需求。 \\n\\nAnother is using Web3 to remove centralized **brokerage companies** by making a decentralized stock exchange.\\n\\n另一种是使用Web3通过建立去中心化的证券交易所来消除中心化的经纪公司。 \\n\\nThere are no small projects. Decentralized applications are being used in areas from ride sharing to online shopping, from online news to online music, from real **estate** to energy trading, and many others.\\n\\n没有小项目。分散式应用程序正在从乘车共享到在线购物、从在线新闻到在线音乐、从房地产到能源交易等许多领域得到应用。 \\n\\nChris Dixon and Packy McCormick also said that the year ahead will show that blockchains can support a lot more applications beyond money and finance.\\n\\n克里斯·迪克森（Chris Dixon）和帕基·麦考密克（Packy McCormick）也表示，未来一年将表明区块链可以支持更多的应用，而不仅仅是货币和金融。 \\n\\nIn 2022, big tech **monopolies** on the internet will be **eroded** by decentralized services. The digital economy of innovators, technologists, and small enterprises will be greatly improved by a cluster of new “web3” technologies, such as tokens.\\n\\n2022年，互联网上的大型技术垄断将被分散的服务所侵蚀。创新者、技术专家和小企业的数字经济将通过一组新的“web3”技术（如代币）得到极大改善。 \\n\\n \\n\\n**4、Final Thoughts（ 最后的想法 ）**\\n\\nThe above explanation is the underlying concept of **Web3** and the technologies that can be built on top of it. One thing we can say about Web3 is that it’s revolutionary and a life-changer for many people.\\n\\n上面的解释是Web3的基本概念，以及可以在此基础上构建的技术。关于Web3，我们可以说的一点是，它是革命性的，对许多人来说，它改变了生活。 \\n\\nWeb3 is the idea of the internet without servers. Web 3.0 is a way to use the Internet that doesn’t need any centralized servers.\\n\\nWeb3是指没有服务器的互联网。Web3.0是一种使用互联网的方式，它不需要任何集中式服务器。 \\n\\nHow? It uses computer by all the users, altogether.\\n\\n怎样做到？所有计算机用户全部参与其中！\\n\\nIt’s like the Internet was in the beginning before anyone made websites.\\n\\n这就像互联网在人们建立网站之前就已经开始了。 \\n\\nWeb3 will be bigger than Web2 because Web2 is all about companies trying to **extract** value from people, while Web3 is all about communities creating value for their people.\\n\\nWeb3将比Web2更大，因为Web2是关于试图从人们身上获取价值的公司，而Web3是关于为他们的人们创造价值的社区。 \\n\\nJust take a look at this tweet! Good luck and please let me know your thoughts. Leave your comments below!\\n\\n看看这条推特！祝你好运，请告诉我你的想法。请在下面留下您的评论！ \\n\\n**说明：**使用风哥邀请码注册，进深度交流群，与VIP群信息60%重合。\\n\\n**个人简介处有一串字母（“比特摩斯”进入，相信你不会错过），+我。**\\n\\n \\n\\n**一、投资心得**\\n\\n1、[不做契约也能暴富？提高认知赚大钱，线投机赚小钱，萤光赔钱！比特摩斯社区为什么禁止一切行为行为？](https://bihu.com/article/1772793847)\\n\\n2、[亚马逊20年\\\\*\\\\*4倍，区块链“奇迹五年之约”有同样的，到潮浪潮的所有学生都没有！](https://bihu.com/article/1259883841)\\n\\n3、[投身一段链，要“知天命，识实务”，要顺从“从0到1”的历史趋势](https://bihu.com/article/1188263408)\\n\\n4、[萌新进币圈，第一防大事不是“骗子”，五个悲痛的受骗案例，教你诈骗/传销/资金盘](https://bihu.com/article/1943120918)\\n\\n5、[以太坊/波卡/Layer2/DeFi，在精彩纷呈的链世界，别“只有3只”，放眼看世界就有未来鸡](https://bihu.com/article/1448459942)\",\"timestamp\":1639532998,\"title\":\"翻译角！什么是Web3，如何跟12岁的孩子解释清楚？（中英对照）\"},\"digest\":\"Ouwy8f7yxVinTqrvrOGdycXfdxLcq7KXqVjIwmngytY\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x8150b557E650d47851dde20Df56a5b4103C13E40\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"alg\\\":\\\"ES256\\\",\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"KOjguDhR6Avcx7Eo81S3_fiBrKoxl3c5KzXixVE5WS4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"jIfWg7xmjuAP3X2D-cd78aZD-uuqyrNcYzXRelrrQgw\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"TOqF5QMk5CXM07U8kf3-zk107gPnr3zE6qvupXn9UyVWTDsO_SoUUrHSnRU60ZzKzjVXSLe5R52gyWOvxNDP3Q\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x285fe3d44fc87f147bd6bb62268c31e56c1fb7eba45d295197f5b26946ea166b2b299633808c4db3dec072664b56c094bbae7f198d0c093dca657914f4642ac11c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"alg\\\":\\\"ES256\\\",\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"KOjguDhR6Avcx7Eo81S3_fiBrKoxl3c5KzXixVE5WS4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"jIfWg7xmjuAP3X2D-cd78aZD-uuqyrNcYzXRelrrQgw\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"Ouwy8f7yxVinTqrvrOGdycXfdxLcq7KXqVjIwmngytY\"}"